    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-06-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="612"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7428</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1926</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose for your strictly
                    confidential information a copy of despatch No. 562 of April 29, 1926, from the
                    American Minister at Peking<note n="52" xml:id="d612fn52">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> in which he discussed the question of the possible withdrawal at some
                    time in the future of the American Army forces stationed at Tientsin. This
                    Department is not now in a position to make definite recommendations in regard
                    to this matter pending the receipt of a further report from Minister MacMurray.
                    I have the honor therefore to request that in view of the peculiar situation at
                    that port no action be taken for the present.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank B. Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
